<br>
If a &quot;high damage, low tank&quot; character ties when fighting a &quot;low damage, high tank&quot; character, all things being equal, the high damage character is the better character.<br>
<br>
Because damage stacks better than tanking does right now.  You cannot &quot;tank&quot; for another player in RvR, while you can do damage &quot;for&quot; another player (on their target).<br>
<br>
Turn intercept, guard, protect and the like into aoe abilities (you intercept all blows in a certain radius, and block attacks on your realmmates, and protect people close to you from being targetted until you are dead), and tweak them up, and that would justify light tanks matching heavy tanks in one on one encounters.<br>
<br>
An alternative is to give light tanks situational defensive abilities that encourage RvR opponents to attack the heavy tanks first, but I can't figure out how to do this without making light tanks better at tanking than heavy tanks.  =/<br>
